message.content:
1. The study involves KSM-66 Ashwagandha and a placebo.
2. The study had 24 participants in the KSM-66 Ashwagandha group.
3. The study had 25 participants in the placebo group.
4. The study measured the mean VO2 max from baseline.
5. The study lasted for 12 weeks.
6. The mean VO2 max increased in the KSM-66 Ashwagandha group at 8 weeks.
7. The mean VO2 max increased in the placebo group at 8 weeks.
8. The increase in the mean VO2 max in the KSM-66 Ashwagandha group at 8 weeks was 4.91.
9. The increase in the mean VO2 max in the placebo group at 8 weeks was 1.42.
10. The mean VO2 max increased in the KSM-66 Ashwagandha group at 12 weeks.
11. The mean VO2 max increased in the placebo group at 12 weeks.
12. The increase in the mean VO2 max in the KSM-66 Ashwagandha group at 12 weeks was 5.67.
13. The increase in the mean VO2 max in the placebo group at 12 weeks was 1.86.
14. The increase in the mean VO2 max from baseline was significantly greater (P < 0.0001) in the KSM-66 Ashwagandha group compared to the placebo group.

messages.content:
Statement: There was a greater increase from baseline (P < 0.0001) in the mean VO2 max with KSM-66 Ashwagandha (n = 24) compared to placebo (n = 25) at 8 weeks (4.91 and 1.42, respectively) and at 12 weeks (5.67 and 1.86 respectively).
